1940 East 36th Street, between Fillmore Ave. and Ave. S, showing the Hendrick I. Lott farmhouse. The right wing is approximately 200 years old. It stood in a hollow about 300 feet northeast of its present location. The large or center portion was occupied in July 1800. In 1922 it was occupied by John B. Lott and Andrew A. Suydam.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
